President Muhammadu Buhari on Wednesday said that the stability of Liberia is a key part of his vision for peace, stability and prosperity in the West African sub-region. He made the assertion while receiving Ms Mawine Diggs, Special Envoy of President George Weah and Liberia’s Acting Foreign Affairs Minister in the presidential villa, He said: “I will continue to do everything possible to ensure the stability of Liberia.” President Buhari commended the Liberian leader for making efforts to maintain good relations with Nigeria. Dozens of children killed in Liberia school fire Buhari to attend Liberia’s independence celebration Friday Liberia calls for peaceful coexistence among African nations George Weah sworn in as Liberian president, completing… ALSO READ: Lyon vows to investigate Bayelsa debt profile under Dickson The Special Envoy said she brought warms greetings from President Weah and the people of Liberia, and thanked President Buhari for his “generous support” to her country. Ms Diggs, who said Nigeria’s support and assistance over time had “impacted positively” on Liberia and its people, added that she brought a special message from President Weah to President Buhari following a recent conversation between both leaders. President Buhari promised to respond positively and promptly to the written message. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
